Chain: BNB Smart Chain (BSC)
Title: Permanent Loss of Funds on Unbound Tokens in TokenRecoverPortal

Description:
`TokenRecoverPortal.recover` marks `recoveredMap[node] = true` before checking whether `TokenHub.recoverBCAsset` actually locks tokens. If the token is not bound, `TokenHub.recoverBCAsset` emits `NotBoundToken` and returns without locking funds, but the recovery leaf is still consumed.

Affected code:
- `TokenRecoverPortal.sol`
```solidity
recoveredMap[node] = true;
ITokenHub(TOKEN_HUB_ADDR).recoverBCAsset(tokenSymbol, msg.sender, amount);
```
- `TokenHub.sol`
```solidity
address contractAddr = bep2SymbolToContractAddr[tokenSymbol];
if (contractAddr == address(0x00)) {
    emit NotBoundToken(tokenSymbol, recipient, amount);
    return;
}
```

Impact claim:
Users can permanently lose the chance to recover tokens if the token is bound only later.

Suggested fix:
Make `recoverBCAsset` return a boolean and only mark the leaf recovered on success.
